			</header>
		<div class="entry-content"><div class="w480"><img id="100000001397683" src="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2012/03/01/opinion/corn/corn-blog480.jpg" alt="" width="480" height="320" /><span class="credit">Olivier Morin/Agence France-Presse â Getty Images</span></div>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Monsanto</strong>: First the good news: France has called for <a href="//www.foodnavigator.com/Financial-Industry/France-calls-on-Commission-to-ban-Monsanto-GM-corn/?utm_source=newsletter_daily&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_campaign=Newsletter%2BDaily&amp;c=e6YrWlMuPoth9URg24Jhxnzj0CtZDBGr">a ban on Monsanto GMO corn</a>. Now the bad: A federal judge in New York has <a href="//www.stltoday.com/business/local/judge-tosses-suit-against-monsanto/article_ef994736-6196-11e1-b46a-0019bb30f31a.html">dismissed a lawsuit</a>, filed by more than 80 farmers and agricultural organizations against Monsanto, which sought to protect organic farmers from litigation if their crops became contaminated by Monsantoâs GMO seeds. From 1997 to 2010, Monsanto sued 144 farmers for patent infringement, a number that the judge said âis hardly significant when compared to the number of farms in the United Statesâ (just try telling that to the 144 farmers).<span id="more-3885"></span></p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Also, the F.D.A. has decided to add <a href="//www.reuters.com/article/2012/02/28/us-fda-statins-idUSTRE81R1O220120228">warnings</a> to the labels of some popular cholesterol-lowering drugs (like Lipitor) to indicate that they may cause higher levels of blood sugar and memory loss. Couldnât have been more than five years ago my G.P. was assuring me they were benign.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Antibiotics in livestock feed DO give rise to antibiotic-resistant germs that can threaten humans: a team from the Translational Genomics Research Institute in Flagstaff <a href="//www.npr.org/blogs/thesalt/2012/02/21/147190101/how-using-antibiotics-in-animal-feed-creates-superbugs">has found</a> that MRSA originated as a human strain that jumped to pigs, where it acquired resistance as a result of drug farm exposure before jumping back to humans. And antibiotics are not just for livestock: <a href="//www.wired.com/wiredscience/2012/02/factory-farm-shrimp/">shrimp farms</a> in South Asia are essentially factory farms, with all that implies â including the overuse of antibiotics.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Missouri Farm Bureau President Blake Hurst has <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2012/02/20/opinion/happy-pigs-and-unhappy-farmers.html?_r=1">a full-throated defense</a> of factory farming that includes a strong endorsement of pig gestation crates. Can we say âdefensiveâ?</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">The Iowa senate has approved an <a href="//blogs.desmoinesregister.com/dmr/index.php/2012/02/28/iowa-senate-approves-ag-gag-bill-opponents-predict-dire-consequences/">âAg Gagâ bill</a> that seeks to prosecute âagricultural production facility fraudâ (obtaining access to a facility under false pretense with the intent to commit an act not authorized by the owner, like video taping animal abuse.) Disgraceful.</p>
<div class="w190 right"><img id="100000001397701" src="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2012/03/01/opinion/fish/fish-articleInline.jpg" alt="" width="190" height="190" /><span class="credit">Dennis W. Ho for The New York Times</span></div>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Fish</strong>: A new partnership to raise $1.5 billion for the world&#8217;s oceans, double marine protected areas and rebuild fish stocks <a href="//www.guardian.co.uk/environment/2012/feb/24/world-bank-coalition-marine-protection">was launched</a> by the World Bank. And Hugh Fearnley-Whittingstall&#8217;s fish discard ban <a href="//www.guardian.co.uk/environment/2012/feb/24/fish-discarding-ban-shunned-mps">has been shunned</a> by British MPs, who argue that British fishermen should be allowed to continue discarding edible fish at sea until at least 2020.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Food System Reform</strong>: <a href="//www.theatlantic.com/health/archive/2012/02/access-to-good-healthy-food-should-be-a-basic-human-right/253349/">Eric Schlosser and Will Allen</a> make the case for a different kind of food system, while last week a Times <a href="//www.nytimes.com/roomfordebate/2012/02/21/the-farm-bill-beyond-the-farm">Room For Debate</a> feature focused on what changes need to be made to the 2012 farm bill. Assemblyman Mike Gatto <a href="//www.foodsafetynews.com/2012/02/cottage-food-bill-introduced-in-california/">introduced a cottage food bill</a> in the California State Assembly, bringing California one step closer to joining a growing number of other states with similar laws. The California Homemade Food Act would allow small food businesses operating out of a private home that produce &#8220;nonpotentially hazardous goods&#8221; (so called &#8220;cottage food operations&#8221;) to comply with fewer regulations.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><strong>Health</strong>: The Obama administration <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2012/02/21/us/politics/new-rules-planned-on-school-vending-machines.html?ref=education">is working on</a> setting nutritional standards for foods that children can buy outside the cafeteria, including in school vending machines. Meanwhile, a 10-year epidemiological study <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2012/02/28/health/research/diet-soft-drinks-linked-to-risk-of-heart-disease.html">has found a link</a> between diet soft drinks and cardiovascular disease.</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Some words of wisdom from <a href="//www.theatlantic.com/health/archive/2012/02/the-importance-of-portion-control/253580/">Marion Nestle</a>: &#8220;If I could teach just one thing about nutrition, it would be this: Larger portions have more calories.&#8221;</p>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody">Finally, for your viewing pleasure: Check out these <a href="//blogs.smithsonianmag.com/food/2012/02/robert-rock-belliveau/">stunning microscopic images</a> of fruits and vegetables.</p>
	</div>
